{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Required patient fields are validated before downstream processing; missing fields return one clear error listing all missing items.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: a unit test of only the validator can pass while orchestration still calls insurance/triage/scheduling. Minimum real failure boundary is request-handler/service wiring that both aggregates missing fields and halts downstream calls.","test_description":"Run intake entrypoint with payload missing name and insurance ID, with downstream collaborators instrumented (or test doubles at module boundary). Assert one validation error lists both missing fields and assert no insurance API call, no triage call, no scheduling write, and no confirmation send.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Date of birth validation rejects future dates, dates older than 150 years, and non-date strings.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"Validation is deterministic logic in a local function/object boundary with no I/O; mocks do not add coverage.","test_description":"Directly test DOB validator with table-driven cases: valid DOB, tomorrow’s date, date older than 150 years, malformed string, and boundary dates (exactly 150 years ago). Assert expected pass/fail and error codes/messages.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.92,"Integration":0.06,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"Insurance eligibility check sends correct patient ID and plan code to payer API and interprets eligible/not eligible/pending correctly.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"REAL-INFRA/MOCK-HIDE: request serialization, HTTP method/path/headers, and response decoding can fail despite in-process mocks passing. Real HTTP boundary is the minimum to catch these failures.","test_description":"Execute insurance client against an HTTP test server that validates received payload fields (patient ID, plan code) and returns representative payer responses for eligible/not_eligible/pending. Assert mapped internal status for each response and verify exact outbound request shape.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.25,"System":0.7,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"If payer API is unreachable, eligibility is marked pending and intake continues.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"REAL-INFRA/MOCK-HIDE: unreachable-host, timeout, DNS, or connection-reset behavior is OS/network/HTTP-level; exception mocks often miss real retry/timeout/error-class handling.","test_description":"Run intake path with payer endpoint pointed to a non-routable or closed port (or controlled server that drops connections). Assert eligibility becomes pending, pipeline proceeds to triage and scheduling, and confirmation is still produced.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.18,"System":0.8,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"AI symptom triage assigns high urgency for emergency symptom combinations (e.g., chest pain + shortness of breath).","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"LLM-DEP: correctness claim is about model classification quality, which depends on real model behavior and can vary across runs/prompts/model updates.","test_description":"Call the real triage model/API on a curated emergency symptom set and a non-emergency contrast set. Assert emergency set is classified high urgency at/above an agreed threshold rate over repeated runs, and log drift/failure cases.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0,"Integration":0.05,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.85,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"Symptom triage returns a cli